text.section:
The governing principles in a record may limit or eliminate the liability of a manager to the unincorporated nonprofit association or its members for damages for any action taken, or for failure to take any action, as a manager, except liability for:
The amount of financial benefit improperly received by a manager;
An intentional infliction of harm on the association or one (1) or more of its members;
An intentional violation of criminal law;
Breach of the duty of loyalty; or
Improper distributions.
